Beginnings of Erlang code for doing webbot-like stuff.

`html:meta(URL)` returns a list of key/value tuples:

* title - The title of the HTML page
* description - Any meta description content (empty string if none)
* firstp - Text content of first paragraph on the page

This depends on the trane SAX HTML parser, with a minor modification
of my own to allow `wget` to be invoked externally.

* [https://github.com/macintux/trane](https://github.com/macintux/trane)
* [https://github.com/massemanet/trane](https://github.com/massemanet/trane)
